.TH EYEMOUSE 1 "May 2026" "tobii4c" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
eyemouse \- Tobii gaze and head tracking mouse controller for X11

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eyemouse

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eyemouse
controls the X11 mouse pointer using realtime gaze tracking,
head pose estimation and blink detection from supported
Tobii Eye Tracker 4C devices.

The utility loads calibration data generated by
.BR eyecalib (1)
and applies adaptive gaze correction, smoothing and drift reduction.

Optional AT-SPI accessibility integration may be used for
assistive desktop interaction and accessibility-aware gaze control.

.SH FEATURES
.IP \[bu] 2
Realtime gaze tracking

.IP \[bu]
Head pose tracking

.IP \[bu]
3D gaze mapping

.IP \[bu]
Blink click support

.IP \[bu]
Barycentric mesh warp

.IP \[bu]
Triangle interpolation

.IP \[bu]
Adaptive edge correction

.IP \[bu]
Pointer smoothing

.IP \[bu]
Drift reduction

.IP \[bu]
Low latency filtering

.IP \[bu]
Dynamic screen resolution handling

.IP \[bu]
Multi-monitor support

.IP \[bu]
Debug telemetry output

.IP \[bu]
Standalone Tobii Engine operation

.IP \[bu]
Optional AT-SPI accessibility integration

.SH OPTIONAL FEATURES

AT-SPI support may provide:

